1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,560
Hello English learners, welcome back to EnglishPod.
英语学习者你们好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:07,080
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:07,080 --> 00:00:08,520
And I'm Erica.
我是Erica。

4
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:12,360
And today we have a fun and scary dialogue.
今天我们有一个既有趣又吓人的对话。

5
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:13,360
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:19,040
This lesson is full of language you can use to talk about being scared.
这节课充满了可以用来谈论害怕的语言。

7
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:25,160
Alright, so we're gonna be looking at a scary lesson today and we have nothing to preview
好的，所以今天我们要看一个吓人的课程，而且我们没什么要预习的。

8
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:30,560
so let's listen to this dialogue and see why everyone is so scared.
所以让我们听听这个对话，看看为什么大家都这么害怕。

9
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:39,160
Hey, why are we at this scary looking mansion?
嘿，我们为什么在这栋看起来很吓人的豪宅前？

10
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:41,560
It's like ultra spooky.
它超级阴森。

11
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:43,320
I told you already Shabby.
我已经告诉过你了，Shabby。

12
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:46,560
The owner of the house says there's a ghost haunting his house.
房主说他的房子里有鬼魂出没。

13
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:52,840
So we have to go in and investigate.
所以我们得进去调查。

14
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:55,880
I don't like this.
我不喜欢这样。

15
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,880
Come on guys, stop being such cowards.
拜托，伙计们，别这么胆小。

16
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:01,120
It's a mystery and an adventure.
这是个谜团，也是一场冒险。

17
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:03,400
This place gives me the creeps.
这地方让我毛骨悚然。

18
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:06,240
Seriously guys, let's get out of here.
说真的，伙计们，我们离开这儿吧。

19
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:09,880
I'm getting goosebumps just being here.
我光是待在这儿就起鸡皮疙瘩了。

20
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:15,440
Shabby is a scaredy cat.
Shabby是个胆小鬼。

21
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:19,880
That laugh came from this room.
那个笑声是从这个房间传来的。

22
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:26,320
Let's go and check it out.
我们进去看看吧。

23
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:30,320
Look, a ghost!
看，有鬼！

24
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,320
Run!
快跑！

25
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:43,920
Well, that sounds really scary but actually it kind of reminds me of another TV show.
嗯，那听起来确实很吓人，但实际上它让我想起了另一个电视节目。

26
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:47,840
Very similar to another TV show but it's different.
和另一个电视节目非常相似，但又不完全一样。

27
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:53,000
Okay, but some interesting language that you can use to talk about things that are scary
好的，但有一些有趣的语言可以用来谈论吓人的事情。

28
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,840
so why don't we look at that now in Language Takeaway.
所以我们不如在“语言要点”环节来看看。

29
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,220
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

30
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:03,160
So let's start with the very first line of our dialogue.
那么我们从对话的第一行开始。

31
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:06,720
Shabby described the mansion to be ultra spooky.
Shabby形容这栋豪宅是“ultra spooky”。

32
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,440
It's ultra spooky.
它超级阴森。

33
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,440
Spooky.
阴森的。

34
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:14,040
So, okay, we've got two interesting words here, ultra and spooky.
所以，这里有两个有趣的词，“ultra”和“spooky”。

35
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:16,320
Now spooky is scary, right?
“Spooky”就是吓人的，对吧？

36
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,480
It's a little bit scary.
它有点吓人。

37
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:22,920
It maybe makes you feel a little bit uncomfortable or maybe it makes you feel a little bit scared.
它可能让你感到有点不舒服，或者让你有点害怕。

38
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,920
Okay, so not very scared.
好的，所以不是非常害怕。

39
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,360
Not super scared.
不是超级害怕。

40
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,840
But ultra spooky.
但是超级阴森。

41
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:33,400
So ultra is another way of saying super or very or really spooky.
所以“ultra”是“super”或“very”或“really spooky”的另一种说法。

42
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,600
So if it's ultra spooky then it's...
所以如果它“ultra spooky”，那就是……

43
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,600
Very scary.
非常吓人。

44
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,600
Okay.
好的。

45
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,840
All right, so our next word.
好了，接下来是我们的下一个词。

46
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:44,160
They said that in the house there is a ghost haunting the house.
他们说那房子里有个鬼魂在作祟。

47
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:47,600
Okay, there is a ghost haunting his house.
好的，有个鬼魂在他的房子里作祟。

48
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:50,480
Okay, so the verb to haunt.
好的，所以动词是“haunt”。

49
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,440
Okay, to haunt.
好的，“haunt”。

50
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:58,560
So the ghost is coming to the house frequently and not letting them live in peace.
所以这个鬼魂经常来这房子，不让他们安宁地生活。

51
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:02,760
When a ghost haunts something, it visits it often and scares it.
当鬼魂作祟时，它经常造访并吓唬人。

52
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:03,760
Exactly.
没错。

53
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:08,440
Now, they were all afraid and they didn't want to go in and so Wilma called everyone
现在，他们都很害怕，不想进去，于是Wilma叫大家

54
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,960
cowards.
懦夫。

55
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,560
Stop being such cowards.
别这么懦弱了。

56
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,560
Cowards.
懦夫。

57
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,520
So, a coward.
所以，“coward”。

58
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:17,200
A coward is a person that's not brave.
“coward”是指不勇敢的人。

59
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:19,400
A person who's scared of everything.
一个什么都怕的人。

60
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,400
Exactly.
没错。

61
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,320
So, they were being cowards.
所以，他们当时表现得很懦弱。

62
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:25,320
They were afraid so that's why they didn't want to go in.
他们害怕，所以不想进去。

63
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:30,960
Well, speaking of being afraid, Shabby said, I'm getting goose bumps.
说到害怕，Shabby说：“我起鸡皮疙瘩了。”

64
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,960
Goose bumps.
鸡皮疙瘩。

65
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,080
To get goose bumps.
起鸡皮疙瘩。

66
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:35,240
All right, to get goose bumps.
好的，起鸡皮疙瘩。

67
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:40,840
Now, goose bumps, it may sound a little bit strange but it's very easy when you're scared
现在，“goose bumps”听起来可能有点奇怪，但很容易理解：当你害怕时

68
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:45,880
or maybe you're cold, the skin on your arms or on your back, it gets a little bit bumpy.
或者觉得冷，你手臂或背上的皮肤会变得有点凹凸不平。

69
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,360
So your skin looks like chicken skin.
所以你的皮肤看起来像鸡皮。

70
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:53,240
Exactly, chicken skin and that's actually how we call it in Spanish, chicken skin but
没错，鸡皮，在西班牙语里我们就是这么叫的，但这里是“goose bumps”，所以我觉得挺相似的。

71
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:55,480
this is goose bumps so I guess it's kind of similar.
鹅。

72
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,480
A goose.
是的，同一个意思。

73
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,360
Yeah, same idea.
鸡皮疙瘩。

74
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,360
Goose bumps.
好的，最后，Scruffy说：“Shabby是个胆小鬼。”

75
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:03,840
All right and finally, Scruffy said, Shabby is a scaredy cat.
胆小鬼。

76
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,920
A scaredy cat.
胆小鬼。

77
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,920
A scaredy cat.
你是个胆小鬼。

78
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:07,320
You're a scaredy cat.
嗯，“scaredy cat”其实不是猫，对吧？

79
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:10,320
Well, a scaredy cat is not really a cat, right?
不，不，不。

80
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,320
No, no, no.
不，不，不。

81
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,120
It's a person who's afraid of everything.
这是一个什么都害怕的人。

82
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,120
Okay.
好的。

83
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,120
Similar to a coward.
类似于懦夫。

84
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,120
But more informal.
但更随意一些。

85
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,120
Much more informal.
非常随意。

86
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:22,240
So somebody is a scaredy cat and I think even a little bit more juvenile.
所以有人是胆小鬼，我觉得甚至更幼稚一点。

87
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,240
As adults.
作为成年人。

88
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,240
So children use it.
所以孩子们会用这个词。

89
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:27,200
Yeah, as adults, you wouldn't say he's a scaredy cat.
是的，作为成年人，你不会说他是胆小鬼。

90
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,200
All right, great.
好的，很棒。

91
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:30,840
So some interesting scary language.
所以是一些有趣的恐怖语言。

92
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:36,560
I think we need to hear it one more time slowed down in the dialogue.
我觉得我们需要再听一遍对话中慢速的版本。

93
