好的，那我们举些例子吧。

142
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,720
I could say, hey Marco, see that guy over there?
我可以说，嘿 Marco，看到那边那个人了吗？

143
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,120
He keeps looking at me.
他一直在看我。

144
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,720
He's giving me the creeps.
他让我毛骨悚然。

145
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:03,920
Okay, or I can say clowns give me the creeps.
好的，或者我可以说小丑让我毛骨悚然。

146
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,920
Oh, that's right.
哦，没错。

147
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,920
You're afraid of clowns.
你害怕小丑。

148
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:06,920
I am afraid of clowns.
我害怕小丑。

149
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,920
They give me the creeps.
他们让我毛骨悚然。

150
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:12,920
All right, well, it's a really helpful, useful phrase to use when you're talking about being
好的，这是一个非常有用、实用的短语，当你谈论

151
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,200
afraid.
害怕时可以用。

152
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:18,000
Now why don't we listen to the dialogue one final time?
现在我们最后听一遍对话吧？

153
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:25,840
Eddie, why are we at this scary looking mansion?
Eddie，我们为什么在这栋看起来吓人的大宅子里？

